author: rooneg
msg: Close a percieved security hole by making the username and password files in
the .svn/auth directory only readable by the user.  This doesn't actually
improve the security of the system, since the auth directory was never
readable by another user, but hopefully this will cut down on the 'but the
password file is world readable!' mails to the dev list.
(open_adm_file): Add parameter 'protection' to indicate the permissions
a created file should have.  This parameter is passed to svn_io_file_open().
svn_wc__open_props): pass APR_OS_DEFAULT as protection to open_adm_file().
